### Class 2 Polynomials

# - some precomputed formulas;

### Note:
# - the P6 has 1716 monoms;
# - the P7 has ... monoms;
# - the s0 term has been added,
#   as it interacts with all other s[i] to form
#   the coefficient of x^(n-1);
# - unfortunately it adds a huge number of additional monoms!
# - alternative:
#  -- compute coefficients without s0;
#  -- shift the polynomial with s0;


